screen( "UNIX I/O" )
\#PCSTDLIB\# - UNIX I/O                                          <stdio.h>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#close\#         \#fileno\#        \#open\#          \#write\#
\#creat\#         \#lseek\#         \#read\#

These functions are used for compatibility with programs written for
the UNIX operating system.

They are essentially identical to the \#GEMDOS\# I/O functions, and use
the same \#GEMDOS handle\#s to identify files and devices.

They use global variable \#errno\# to report errors (as opposed to
returning \#BIOS/GEMDOS Error Code\#s).
\end

