Function puts character <c> back into the stream buffer to be read by
a subsequent read operation.  The last character read is replaced and
the stream position is decremented (until the beginning of the buffer
is reached).

It returns the character, or EOF on error.

See also \#Standard I/O\# and \#fgetc\#().
\end

