void* memset( void *buf, int c, \#size_t\# n );

  <buf> points to the buffer to be filled.
  <c> is a character (0-255) passed as an int.
  <n> is the number of bytes to copy.


Function set <n> bytes in <buf> to <c>.
It returns a pointer to <buf>.

See also \#String & Character\#, \#calloc\#(), \#strset\#() and \#strnset\#().
\end

