screen( capsensitive("Giaccess") )
#include <tos.h>

char Giaccess( char data, int regno );

  <data> byte to be written to register.
  <regno> is a register number:
          0-15 read register
          128-143 write to register 0-15 ( | with 0x80).


Function reads or writes to a register on the \link("%%GLOBAL%%")YM2149\# Sound Chip.

Note: Port B (reg 15) is the Centronix port (data lines).
