screen( capsensitive("Offgibit") )
#include <tos.h>

void Offgibit( int bitno );

  <bitno> is the bit number:
          0 = Floppy side 1 select
          1 = Floppy drive 0 deselect
          2 = Floppy drive 1 deselect
          3 = RTS low (RS232/Modem 1 port)
          4 = DTR low (RS232/Modem 1 port)
          5 = Printer Port Strobe low
          6 = Internal speaker disable (TT)
              Monitor Jack GPO Pin (Falcon)
          7 = LAN port select (TT)
              IDE Drive off (Falcon)


Function clears one of the bits on Port A of the \link("%%GLOBAL%%")YM2149\# sound chip.

