  <bitno> is the bit number:
          0 = Floppy side 0 select
          1 = Floppy drive 0 select
          2 = Floppy drive 1 select
          3 = RTS high (RS232/Modem 1 port)
          4 = DTR high (RS232/Modem 1 port)
          5 = Printer Port Strobe high
          6 = Internal speaker enable (TT)
              Monitor Jack GPO Pin (Falcon)
          7 = Serial 2 select (TT)
              IDE Drive on (Falcon)


Function sets one of the bits on Port A of the \link("%%GLOBAL%%")YM2149\# sound chip.

