screen( capsensitive("Xbtimer") )
#include <tos.h>

void Xbtimer( int timer, int control, int data, void (*vector)() );

  <timer> is the timer number:
          0 = A (DMA sound frame counter - STE, TT and Falcon)
          1 = B (horizontal sync counter)
          2 = C (200 Hz system clock)
          3 = D (Modem 1 Baud Rate Generator)
  <control> will be written to the control register.
  <data> will be written to the data register.
  <vector> is an interrupt handler (usually written in assembly).


Function allows you to set one of the interrupt timers on the MFP.
See \link("%%GLOBAL%%")MFP Timer Registers\# for details.  Max delay is 21 msec.

\#XBIOS Opcode\# 31

See also \#XBIOS Misc\# and \#evnt_timer\#().
\end

screen( capsensitive("Dosound") )
#include <tos.h>

void *Dosound( void *buf );

  <buf> is a string of sound chip commands:
        0-15: Store next byte into corresponding register.
        128 = Load next byte into counter.
        129 = Use next three bytes as follows:
              The counter is loaded into the register specified by the
              first byte.
              The counter is incremented by the second byte.
              Repeat until the counter equals the third byte.
        130-255: If next byte is zero, terminate.
              Otherwise, wait for that many vblanks and continue.


Function allows you to perform several sound chip operations using the
vertical blank routine for a delay timer.

When <buf> = (void*) -1L, it returns the address of the current sound
buffer, or 0L in none in use.

Note: Will cause MultiTOS to crash prior to \#MiNT Version\# 1.08

\#XBIOS Opcode\# 32

See also \#XBIOS Sound\# and \#Dosound Examples\#.
\end

