#include <tos.h>

int Setprt( int config );

  <config> is the new printer configuration, or -1 to keep old value.


Function sets and/or gets the printer configuration.  It returns the
old configuration value.  (Only relevant to screen dumps.)

   Bit   When 0         When 1
   ---   -------------  ------------------
    0    Dot Matrix     Daisy Wheel
    1    Color          Monochrome
    2    Atari Printer  Epson Printer (graphics)
    3    Draft          Final         (dot density)
    4    Parallel Port  Serial Port
    5    Form Feed      Single Sheet

