long VgetSize( int mode );

  <mode> is the Falcon color mode bit flags:
         BPS1  = monochrome
         BPS2  = 2 bit planes = 4 colors
         BPS4  = 4 bit planes = 16 colors
         BPS8  = 8 bit planes = 256 colors
         BPS16 = 16 bits/pixel RGB colors

         COL80 = 80 columns 
         COL40 = 40 columns
         VGA_FALCON = multisync monitor
         TV = TV or video monitor
         PAL = PAL (as opposed to NTSC) TV
         OVERSCAN = overscan on
         STMODES = ST compatible resolutions
         VERTFLAG = interlace or double line on


Function returns the size required for a screen buffer using the given
video mode.

Note: Not all bit flag combinations are legal (or meaningful).
      Available when '_VDO' cookie >= 0x30000L (see \#Cookies\#).

\#XBIOS Opcode\# 91

See also \#XBIOS Video\# and \#VsetScreen\#().
\end

