screen( capsensitive("Dsp_InStream") )
#include <tos.h> 

void Dsp_InStream( char *data_in, long block_size, long num_blocks,
                   long *blocks_done );

  <data_in> points to the packed input data.
  <block_size> is the number of DSP words to send per interrupt.
  <num_blocks> is the number of blocks to process.
  <blocks_done> points to a \link("%%GLOBAL%%")volatile\# variable which will be
                updated until (blocks_done == num_blocks).


Function transfers bytewise packed data to the Digital Signal
Processor.  It does not wait for the transfer to complete.

Note: Available when the '_SND' cookie has bit 4 set (see \#Cookies\#).

\#XBIOS Opcode\# 99

See also \#XBIOS Sound\# and \link("%%GLOBAL%%")DSP56001\#.
\end

screen( capsensitive("Dsp_OutStream") )
#include <tos.h> 

void Dsp_OutStream( char *data_out, long block_size, long num_blocks,
                    long *blocks_done );

  <data_out> is a buffer array to store the packed output data.
  <block_size> is the number of DSP words to receive per interrupt.
  <num_blocks> is the number of blocks to process.
  <blocks_done> points to a \link("%%GLOBAL%%")volatile\# variable which will be
                updated until (blocks_done == num_blocks).


Function transfers bytewise packed data from the Digital Signal
Processor.  It does not wait for the transfer to complete.

Note: Available when the '_SND' cookie has bit 4 set (see \#Cookies\#).

\#XBIOS Opcode\# 99

See also \#XBIOS Sound\# and \link("%%GLOBAL%%")DSP56001\#.
\end

