         THIN_CROSS, THICK_CROSS, OUTLN_CROSS or:
         USER_DEF - use mouse form specified by <faddr>
         M_OFF    - turn off mouse cursor
         M_ON     - turn on mouse cursor
  <faddr> points to an application specified mouse form description
          when <form> = USER_DEF.  Use a NULL pointer otherwise.


Function changes the mouse form.
It returns a positive number normally, or 0 on an error.

\#AES Opcode\# 78

See also \#Graphics\#, \#vsc_form\#(), \#v_show_c\#() and \#v_hide_c\#().
\end

