void vst_height( int handle, int height,
                 int *char_width, int *char_height,
                 int *cell_width, int *cell_height );

  <handle> is the \#VDI Handle\#.
  <height> is the desired character height in \#VDI Coordinates\#.
           System font sizes:
            4  (1-4) = small font (6x6)
            6 (5-12) = low/med res font (8x8)
            13 (13+) = high res font (8x16)
  <char_width> returns the character width implemented.
  <char_height> returns the character height implemented.
  <cell_width> returns the cell width implemented.
  <cell_height) returns the cell height implemented.


Function changes size of the font.  (A cell is a square box large
enough to hold a character.  See \#graf_handle\#.)

\#VDI Opcode\# 12

See also \#VDI Attributes\#, \#v_gtext\#() and \#v_justified\#().
