           [0] = line style (see \#vsl_type\#).
           [1] = line color index (see \#vsl_color\#).
           [2] = writing mode (see \#vswr_mode\#).
           [3] = Starting end style (see \#vsl_ends\#).
           [4] = Other end style.
           [5] = line width (see \#vsl_width\#).


Function returns the line attributes.

\#VDI Opcode\# 35

See also \#VDI Inquire\#, \#v_pline\#(), \#v_arc\#(), \#v_ellarc\#() and \#v_rbox\#().
\end

screen( capsensitive("vqm_attributes") )
#include <vdi.h>

void vqm_attributes( int handle, int *attrib);

  <handle> is the \#VDI Handle\#.
