           [0] = marker symbol (see \#vsm_type\#).
           [1] = marker color index (see \#vsm_color\#).
           [2] = writing mode (see \#vswr_mode\#).
           [3] = marker width in \#VDI Coordinates\#.
           [4] = marker height (see \#vsm_height\#).


Function returns the marker attributes.

\#VDI Opcode\# 36

See also \#VDI Inquire\# and \#v_pmarker\#().
\end

screen( capsensitive("vqf_attributes") )
#include <vdi.h>

void vqf_attributes( int handle, int *attrib);

  <handle> is the \#VDI Handle\#.
