\#VDI Subopcode\# 5,20

See also \#VDI Printer Escapes\# and \#v_updwk\#().
\end

screen( capsensitive("v_output_window") )
#include <vdi.h>

void v_output_window( int handle, int *xyarray );

  <handle> is the \#VDI Handle\#.
  <xyarray> is a 4 entry int array defining a rectangle:
            [0] = x coordinate of left (or right) edge.
            [1] = y coordinate of bottom (or top) edge.
            [2] = x coordinate of right (or left) edge.
            [3] = y coordinate of top (or bottom) edge.


Function outputs the specified rectangle to the printer.
(Applies only to GDOS printer device workstations.)
Does not guarantee than consecutive windows will abut.

\#VDI Subopcode\# 5,21

See also \#VDI Printer Escapes\#, \#VDI Coordinates\# and \#v_updwk\#().
\end

