Function restores the screen image using the sprite save buffer
created by a previous call to \#draw_sprite\#().

See also \#Line A\#.
\end

screen( capsensitive("draw_sprite") )
#include <linea.h>

void draw_sprite( int x, int y, \#SDB\# *sdb, \#SSB\# *ssb );

  <x> is the x location of the hot spot.
  <y> is the y location of the hot spot.
  <sdb> is the address of a sprite definition block.
  <ssb> is the address of a sprite save buffer.


Function draws a 16x16 pixel image to the screen and saves the
original screen image to the sprite save buffer.

See also \#Line A\#.
\end

screen( capsensitive("set_fg_bp") )
