void set_wrt_mode( int mode );

  <mode> is the writing mode: REPLACE, TRANS, XOR or INVERS


Function sets the writing mode for \#draw_line\#(), \#horizontal_line\#(),
\#filled_rect\#() and \#filled_polygon\#().

See also \#Line A\#.
\end

screen( capsensitive("set_pattern") )
#include <linea.h>

void set_pattern( int *pattern, int mask, int multifill );

  <pattern> is the address of the fill pattern array.
            Each line can use a different 16 bit pattern.
            The number of patterns must be a power of 2.
  <mask> is the number of patterns minus 1;
        (y & mask) is used as the pattern index for that line.
  <multifill> multiple bit plane flag: 0 = monochrome.


Function sets the fill pattern for \#filled_rect\#() and \#filled_polygon\#().

See also \#Line A\#.
\end

screen( capsensitive("set_clip") )
#include <linea.h>

void set_clip( int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2, int clip );

