screen( capsensitive("BGI"),
		capsensitive("PCBGILIB") )
PCBGILIB - Borland Graphics Interface                     <graphics.h>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
... is a graphics package which is portable to Turbo C on an IBM PC.
It works by using different graphics drivers for different graphics
hardware.

  \#BGI Control\#    - graphics drivers and modes
  \#BGI Primitives\# - draw lines, curves and fill area
  \#BGI Attributes\# - features for primitives
  \#BGI Text\#       - fonts
  \#BGI Raster\#     - pixel operations
  \#BGI Color\#      - color palette
  \#BGI Service\#    - misc. functions

You MUST call \#initgraph\#() and \#closegraph\#() to use BGI graphics.

All coordinates are in pixels and degrees.
BGI color indexes are mapped to hardware color indexes.

This version does not support mouse, icon or menu operations.

See also \#BGI Example\# and \#VDI\#.
\end

screen( "BGI Control" )
\#BGI\# Control                                               <graphics.h>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#initgraph\#         - initialize graphics driver (REQUIRED)
\#closegraph\#        - release graphics driver (REQUIRED)

\#graphresult\#       - return error code
\#getmaxx\#           - return screen width
\#getmaxy\#           - return screen height

\#detectgraph\#       - return graphics hardware/driver.
\#installuserdriver\# - load new graphics driver (file).
\#registerbgidriver\# - load new graphics driver (function).

\#getmoderange\#      - return min & mix graphics mode for any driver.
\#getmaxmode\#        - return max graphics mode for current driver.
\#getgraphmode\#      - return currrent graphics mode for driver.
\#setgraphmode\#      - change/restore graphics mode for driver.
\#restorecrtmode\#    - switch to text mode.

See also \#BGI Primitives\#, \#BGI Attributes\#, \#BGI Text\#, \#BGI Raster\#,
         \#BGI Color\# and \#BGI Service\#.
\end

screen( "BGI Primitives" )
\#BGI\# Graphics Primitives                                   <graphics.h>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#getx\#, \#gety\#  - return cursor location.
\#lineto\#      - draw line from cursor location.
\#moveto\#      - move cursor. 
\#linerel\#     - draw line relative to cursor location.
\#moverel\#     - move cursor relative to old location.

\#line\#        - draw a line connecting two points.
\#drawpoly\#    - draw a line connecting several points.
\#rectangle\#   - draw a box (outline).

\#circle\#      - draw a circle.
\#arc\#         - draw part of a circle.
\#ellipse\#     - draw an elliptical arc.

\#bar\#         - draw a filled box with border.
\#bar3d\#       - draw a filled box with 3D border.
\#fillellipse\# - draw a filled ellipse.
\#fillpoly\#    - draw a filled polygon.
\#pieslice\#    - draw a filled circular arc.
\#sector\#      - draw a filled elliptical arc.

\#floodfill\#   - fill area surrounded by specified color.

See also \#BGI Control\#, \#BGI Attributes\#, \#BGI Text\#, \#BGI Raster\#,
         \#BGI Color\# and \#BGI Service\#.
\end

screen( "BGI Attributes" )
\#BGI\# Graphics Attributes                                   <graphics.h>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#setviewport\#     - set clipping rectangle.
\#getviewsettings\# - return current clipping rectangle.

\#graphdefaults\#   - reset all attributes to default values.
\#setwritemode\#    - set write mode for lines.
\#setlinestyle\#    - set style and thickness for lines.
\#setfillstyle\#    - set pattern index and color for fill.
\#setfillpattern\#  - set user defined fill pattern.

\#getarccoords\#    - return endpoints and center for last arc.
\#getlinesettings\# - return style and thickness for lines.
\#getfillsettings\# - return pattern index and color for fill.

See also \#BGI Control\#, \#BGI Primitives\#, \#BGI Text\#, \#BGI Raster\#,
         \#BGI Color\# and \#BGI Service\#.
\end

screen( "BGI Text" )
\#BGI\# Text                                                  <graphics.h>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#outtext\#         - write string at current cursor location.
\#outtextxy\#       - write string at specified x,y location.

\#settextstyle\#    - select font, direction and size.
\#setusercharsize\# - scale factor for stroke fonts (when size = 0).
\#settextjustify\#  - location of text relative to cursor.

\#gettextsettings\# - return font, direction, etc.
\#textheight\#      - return height required for given string.
\#textwidth\#       - return width required for given string.

\#installuserfont\# - load new font (file).
\#registerbgifont\# - load new font (function).

See also \#BGI Control\#, \#BGI Primitives\#, \#BGI Attributes\#, \#BGI Raster\#,
         \#BGI Color\# and \#BGI Service\#.
\end

screen( "BGI Raster" )
\#BGI\# Raster                                                <graphics.h>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#cleardevice\#    - clear screen for graphics.
\#clearviewport\#  - clear screen inside clipping rectangle.

\#imagesize\#      - return size of bitmap needed.
\#getimage\#       - copy screen to bitmap.
\#putimage\#       - copy bitmap to screen.

\#getpixel\#       - return color index for a single pixel.
\#putpixel\#       - set the color index for a single pixel.

See also \#BGI Control\#, \#BGI Primitives\#, \#BGI Attributes\#, \#BGI Text\#,
         \#BGI Color\# and \#BGI Service\#.
\end

screen( "BGI Color" )
\#BGI\# Color                                                 <graphics.h>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#getmaxcolor\#       - return maximum BGI color index.
\#getpalettesize\#    - return size of \#palettetype\# structure.

\#setcolor\#          - set BGI color index for lines and text.
\#setbkcolor\#        - set background BGI color index.

\#getcolor\#          - return current BGI color index.
\#getbkcolor\#        - return background BGI color index.

\#setpalette\#        - change one color definition.
\#setallpalette\#     - change all color definitions.
\#setrgbpalette\#     - change one color using RGB values (IBM only).

\#getpalette\#        - return current palette definition.
\#getdefaultpalette\# - return default palette definition.

See also \#BGI Control\#, \#BGI Primitives\#, \#BGI Attributes\#, \#BGI Text\#,
         \#BGI Raster\# and \#BGI Service\#.
\end

screen( "BGI Service" )
\#BGI\# Service                                               <graphics.h>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#grapherrormsg\#   - return text error message.
\#getdrivername\#   - return graphics driver name.
\#getmodename\#     - return graphics mode name.

\#_graphgetmem\#    - BGI portable \#malloc\#.
\#_graphfreemem\#   - BGI portable \#free\#.

\#setaspectratio\#  - set aspect ratio for pixels (IBM only).
\#getaspectratio\#  - return aspect ratio for pixels (IBM only).

\#setactivepage\#   - page to be drawn to (IBM only).
\#setvisualpage\#   - page to be displayed (IBM only).
\#setgraphbufsize\# - change BGI buffer size (IBM only).

See also \#BGI Control\#, \#BGI Primitives\#, \#BGI Attributes\#, \#BGI Text\#,
         \#BGI Raster\# and \#BGI Color\#.
\end

screen( "BGI Example" )
#include <graphics.h>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <ext.h>

int main (void)
 {
  int driver,mode,err;

  driver = VDI;
  mode = VDIMODE;
  \#initgraph\#(&driver, &mode, "E:\\\\pure_c");
  err = \#graphresult\#();
  if(err) {
    \#puts\#(\#grapherrormsg\#(err));
    return(err);
   }
  \#settextjustify\#(LEFT_TEXT, TOP_TEXT);
  \#outtext\#("Hello world!");
  \#getch\#();                               /* wait for keyboard event */
  \#closegraph\#();
  return(\#graphresult\#());
 }
\end

screen( "BGI Default Palette" )
BGI Default Palette                                       <graphics.h>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
 0  BLACK              8  DARKGRAY
 1  BLUE               9  LIGHTBLUE
 2  GREEN             10  LIGHTGREEN
 3  CYAN              11  LIGHTCYAN
 4  RED               12  LIGHTRED
 5  MAGENTA           13  LIGHTMAGENTA
 6  BROWN             14  YELLOW
 7  LIGHTGRAY         15  WHITE
\end

screen( capsensitive("arc") )
#include <graphics.h>

void arc( int x, int y, int stangle, int endangle, int radius );

  <x> is the horizontal position for the center of the circle.
  <y> is the vertical position for the center of the circle.
  <stangle> is the starting angle in degrees.
  <endangle> is the ending angle in degrees.
  <radius> is the radius of the circle.


Function draws a circular arc counter-clockwise (increasing angles)
from <stangle> to <endangle>.

VDI: \#v_arc\#()

See also \#BGI Primitives\#, \#setlinestyle\#(), \#setcolor\#() & \#graphresult\#().
\end

screen( capsensitive("bar") )
#include <graphics.h>

void bar( int left, int top, int right, int bottom );

  <left> is the horizontal position of the left side.
  <top> is the vertical position of the top.
  <right> is the horizontal position of the right side.
  <bottom> is the vertical position of the bottom.


Function draws a filled rectangular area with an outline.

VDI: \#v_bar\#().

See also \#BGI Primitives\#, \#setfillstyle\#(), \#setfillpattern\#() & \#graphresult\#().
\end

screen( capsensitive("bar3d") )
#include <graphics.h>

void bar3d( int left, int top, int right, int bottom,
            int depth, int topflag );

  <left> is the horizontal position of the left side.
  <top> is the vertical position of the top.
  <right> is the horizontal position of the right side.
  <bottom> is the vertical position of the bottom.
  <depth> is the thickness of the border in pixels.
  <topflag> is TRUE (!0) to draw the top & right borders,
            or FALSE (0) to draw only the right border.


Function draws a filled rectangular area with a 3D border on the top
and right sides (using the current line color).

See also \#BGI Primitives\#, \#setcolor\#(), \#setfillstyle\#(), \#setfillpattern\#() & \#graphresult\#().
