screen( capsensitive("drawpoly") )
#include <graphics.h>

void drawpoly( int numpoints, int *polypoints );

  <numpoints> is the number of points to draw.
  <polypoints> is an array of x,y locations:
               [0] is the first x location
               [1] is the first y location
               [2] is the second x location
               [3] is the second y location
               ...
               [2*numpoints - 1] is the last y location.


Function draws a segmented line connecting several points.
To draw a closed polygon, the first and last points must be at the
same location.

VDI: \#v_pline\#()

See also \#BGI Primitives\#, \#setlinestyle\#(), \#setcolor\#(), \#setwritemode\#() &
         \#graphresult\#().
