  <top> is the y coordinate of the top edge.
  <right> is the x coordinate of the right edge.
  <botton> is the y coordinate of the bottom edge.


Function returns the size (in bytes) of the buffer needed to store a
bitmap for the specified rectangle.

See also \#BGI Raster\# & \#graphresult\#().
\end

screen( capsensitive("initgraph") )
#include <graphics.h>

void initgraph( int *graphdriver, int *graphmode, char *pathtodriver );

  <graphdriver> is the driver id, or DETECT to check the graphics
                hardware and return new values.
  <graphmode> is the graphics mode.
  <pathtodriver> is a NULL terminated string containing the pathname
                 for the folder containing the drivers (*.BGI).


Function initializes graphics, sets the default attributes, and clears
the screen (using the default background color).

The values for <graphdriver> and <graphmode> will be changed on return
when <graphdriver> == DETECT initially.

Note: When using a registered driver (see \#registerbgidriver\#) use ""
      for <pathtodriver>, not a NULL pointer!  (Atari only)

See also \#BGI Control\#, \#BGI Example\# and \#Pathnames\#.
\end

