screen( capsensitive("putimage") )
#include <graphics.h>

void putimage( int left, int top, void *bitmap, int op );

  <left> is the x coordinate of the left edge.
  <top> is the y coordinate of the top edge.
  <bitmap> is an array containing a raster image (previously created
           using \#getimage\#).
  <op> is the writing option:
       COPY_PUT replaces the entire rectangle.
       XOR_PUT performs a bitwise exclusive or.
              (An image XORed with itself is erased).
       OR_PUT performs a bitwise or.
       AND_PUT performs a bitwise and (mask).
       NOT_PUT replaces the entire rectangle with inverse video.
       

Function writes a bitmap array to the screen.

VDI: \#vro_cpyfm\#()

See also \#BGI Raster\# and \#graphresult\#().
\end

