screen( "PGETFLAGS" )
Get PRGFLAGS                                        \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( PGETFLAGS, (long) &flags, f );

  <flags> returns the PRGFLAGS for the process.
  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a process pseudo-file.


PRGFLAGS control access to \link("%%GLOBAL%%")TT RAM\#.

See also \#MiNT Process\#.
\end

screen( "PTRACEGFLAGS" )
Get Trace Flags                                     \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( PTRACEGFLAGS, (long) &flags, f );

  <flags> returns the Trace Flags (int) for the process.
  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a process pseudo-file.


Trace flags are used to implement a process one instruction at a time,
sending a SIGCHLD signal to the tracer.

See also \#MiNT Process\#.
\end

screen( "PTRACESFLAGS" )
Set Trace Flags                                     \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( PTRACESFLAGS, (long) &flags, f );

  <flags> contains the new Trace Flags (int) for the process.
  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a process pseudo-file.


Trace flags are used to implement a process one instruction at a time,
sending a SIGCHLD signal to the tracer.

See also \#MiNT Process\#.
\end

screen( "PTRACEGO" )
GO - Trace Mode                                     \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
