Function is used to continue a process in flow trace mode.

See also \#MiNT Process\# and \#Signals\#.
\end

screen( "PTRACESTEP" )
Step - Trace Mode                                   \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( PTRACESTEP, 0L, f );

  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a process pseudo-file.


Function allows process to execute one instruction in flow trace mode.

See also \#MiNT Process\#.
\end

screen( "PLOADINFO" )
Process Information                                 \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( PLOADINFO, (long) &info, f );

  <info> is a ploadinfo structure (below).
  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a process pseudo-file.


Function returns information about process launching.

struct ploadinfo {
  int fnamelen;    /* length of fname buffer                   */
  char *cmdlin;    /* 128 byte buffer to return command line   */
  char *fname;     /* buffer to return full pathname of parent */
 } info;

See also \#MiNT Process\# and \#Pathnames\#
\end

screen( "TIOCGETP" )
Get TTY Parameters                                  \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( TIOCGETP, (long) &parm, f );

  <parm> is a buffer to return a sgttyb structure (below).
  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a TTY device driver.


Function returns information about a TTY device driver.

struct sgttyb {
  char sg_ispeed;    /* reserved             */
  char sg_ospeed;    /* reserved             */
  char sg_erase;     /* erase character      */
  char sg_kill;      /* line erase character */
  int  sg_flags;     /* bit flags            */
 } parm;

See also \#MiNT Device\#.
\end

screen( "TIOCSETP" )
Set TTY Parameters                                  \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( TIOCSETP, (long) &parm, f );

  <parm> is a sgttyb structure (below).
  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a TTY device driver.


Function resets TTY device driver parameters.
(You should modify the values obtained using \#TIOCGETP\#.)

struct sgttyb {
  char sg_ispeed;    /* reserved             */
  char sg_ospeed;    /* reserved             */
  char sg_erase;     /* erase character      */
  char sg_kill;      /* line erase character */
  int  sg_flags;     /* bit flags            */
 } parm;

See also \#MiNT Device\#.
\end

screen( "TIOCGETC" )
Get TTY Control Characters                          \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( TIOCGETC, (long) &chrs, f );

  <chrs> is a buffer to return a tchars structure (below).
  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a TTY device driver.


Function returns control codes for a TTY device driver.

struct tchars {
  char t_intrc;     /* interrupt - SIGINT  */
  char t_quitc;     /* abort - SIGKILL     */
  char t_startc;    /* start output flow   */
  char t_stopc;     /* stop output flow    */
  char t_eofc;      /* end of file         */
  char t_brkc;      /* end of line         */
 } chrs;

See also \#MiNT Device\# and \#Signals\#.
\end

screen( "TIOCSETC" )
Set TTY Control Characters                          \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( TIOCSETC, (long) &chrs, f );

  <chrs> is a tchars structure (below).
  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a TTY device driver.


Function resets control codes for a TTY device driver.

struct tchars {
  char t_intrc;     /* interrupt - SIGINT  */
  char t_quitc;     /* abort - SIGKILL     */
  char t_startc;    /* start output flow   */
  char t_stopc;     /* stop output flow    */
  char t_eofc;      /* end of file         */
  char t_brkc;      /* end of line         */
 } chrs;

See also \#MiNT Device\# and \#Signals\#.
\end

screen( "TIOCGLTC" )
Get Extended TTY Control Characters                 \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( TIOCGLTC, (long) &chrs, f );

  <chrs> is a buffer to return a ltchars structure (below).
  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a TTY device driver.


Function returns extended control codes for a TTY device driver.

struct ltchars {
  char t_suspc;    /* immediate SIGTSTP            */
  char t_dsuspc;   /* SIGTSTP when read by process */
  char t_rprtc;    /* repeat input line            */
  char t_flushc;   /* flush output buffer          */
  char t_werasc;   /* erase a word                 */
  char t_lnextc;   /* quotes a character           */
 } chrs;

See also \#MiNT Device\# and \#Signals\#.
\end

screen( "TIOCSLTC" )
Set Extended TTY Control Characters                 \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
