screen( "TIOCGFLAGS" )
Get Serial Bit Configuration                        \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( TIOCGFLAGS, (long) &conf, f );

  <conf> returns the data & stop bit conficuration:
         Bits 0-1 = stops bits (0=none, 1=one, 2 = 1.5, 3=two).
         Bits 3-5 = data bits (0=eight, 4=seven, 8=six, 12=five). 
  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a serial device driver.


See also \#MiNT Device\# and \#Rsconf\#().
\end

screen( "TIOCSFLAGS" )
Set Serial Bit Configuration                        \#Fcntl Command Code\#
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#Fcntl\#( TIOCSFLAGS, (long) &conf, f );

  <conf> is the new data & stop bit configuration:
         Bits 0-1 = stops bits (0=none, 1=one, 2 = 1.5, 3=two).
         Bits 3-5 = data bits (0=eight, 4=seven, 8=six, 12=five). 
  <f> is an open \#I/O handle\# for a serial device driver.


See also \#MiNT Device\# and \#Rsconf\#().
\end

