screen( capsensitive("va_list") )
#include <stdarg.h>

  typedef void* va_list;

Specifically, va_list points to a data structure consisting of all
the variables in the order they are used.

For example:

struct {
  int c;      /* char is converted to int */
  double f;   /* float is converted to double */
  char* s;
} list;

  \#vprintf\#( "%c %f %s", &list );

corresponds to:

  \#printf\#( "%c %f %s", list.c, list.f, list.s );

\end

