screen( "VDI Control Array" )
VDI Control Array
----------------------------------------------------------------------
contrl[0]  - \#VDI Opcode\# for function
contrl[1]  - number entries in ptsin[]
contrl[2]  - number entries in ptsout[]
contrl[3]  - number entries in intin[]
contrl[4]  - number entries in intout[]
contrl[5]  - \#VDI Subopcode\# for function (default = 0).
contrl[6]  - workstation handle
...        - reserved

See also \#VDIPARBLK\# and \#VDIPB\#.
\end

screen( capsensitive("MFDB") )
\#VDI Raster\# Memory Form Definition Block                        <vdi.h>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
typedef struct
 {
  void *fd_addr;     /* buffer address or NULL for device         */
  int  fd_w;         /* width in pixels                           */
  int  fd_h;         /* height in pixels                          */
  int  fd_wdwidth;   /* width in words (fd_w + 15)/16             */
  int  fd_stand;     /* 0 = device specific format, 1 = standard  */
  int  fd_nplanes;   /* number of bit planes (log2 number colors) */
  int  fd_r1;        /* reserved (0)                              */
  int  fd_r2;        /* reserved (0)                              */
  int  fd_r3;        /* reserved (0)                              */
 } MFDB;

Buffer must be (fd_wdwidth * fd_h * fd_nplanes) words is size, word
alligned.

When fd_addr == 0L, all other entries are ignored.

Monochrome and duochrome use 1 bit plane.
ST Medium Res uses 2 bit planes.
ST Low and TT Medium Res use 4 bit planes.
TT Low Res uses 8 bit planes.

Pixels refer to raster coordinates (see \#VDI Coordinates\#).
\end

screen( "Metafile Format" )
Metafile Format (int array)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Header format:
 [0] = 0xFFFF (magic)
 [1] = length of header (words)
 [2] = version number (minor + 100 * major)
 [3] = NDC/RC flag (0=NDC, 2=RC.  See \#VDI Coordinates\#)
 [4] = min_x (see \#v_meta_extents\#, default is 0).
 [5] = min_y  "
 [6] = max_x  "
 [7] = max_y  "
 [8] = page width in units of 0.0001 meters.
 [9] = page height in usint of 0.0001 meters.
[10] = llx (see \#vm_coords\#, default is 0)
[11] = lly  "
[12] = urx  "
[13] = ury  "

Command format:
[0] = opcode
[1] = vertex count (2 words per vertex)
[2] = parameter count
[3] = sub opcode
[4...] = vertex coordinates (x,y,x,y,...)
[n+4...] = parameters

Text is passed one character per word (ASCII value in lower byte).
\end

screen( "IMG" )
Bit Image Format
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Header format (int array):
  [0] = image file version number
  [1] = header length in words (8)
  [2] = number of color bit planes
  [3] = pattern definition size in bytes (1-8)
  [4] = source pixel width in microns
  [5] = source pixel height in microns
  [6] = scan line width in pixels
  [7] = number of scan lines

Scan line format:
  Byte 0 = 0  (sync code)
  Byte 1 = 0
  Byte 2 = 0xFF
  Byte 3 = number of identical scan lines)
  Byte 4...n   = first plane
  Byte n+1...m = second bit plane
  ...

Solid run (1 byte):
  bit 15    = pixel on (1) or off (0)
  bits 0-14 = number of consecutive bits

Pattern run:
  Byte 0    = 0
  Byte 1    = length of run in patterns (see header for pattern size)
  Byte 2... = bit pattern

Bit Stream:
  Byte 0    = 0x80
  Byte 1    = length of run in bytes (8 pixels)
  Byte 2... = raster bits
\end

